persons:
    person-anguy:
        properties:
            name:
                value: "Anguy"
                fields:
                    given: "Anguy"
            gender: male
        notes: "Unheralded commoner from the Dornish Marches. Won the archery competition at the Hand's tourney in King's Landing (~298 AC), outshooting Ser Balon Swann and Jalabhar Xho at one hundred paces. Ned Stark offered him a position with the Hand's guard, but Anguy refused, being flush with wine, victory, and prize money."
